    <h1>Data Abstraction</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Abelson &amp; Sussman &middot; 1996 &middot; <a href="https://mitp-content-server.mit.edu/books/content/sectbyfn/books_pres_0/6515/sicp.zip/full-text/book/book-Z-H-14.html#%_sec_2.1">SICP &sect;2.1</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Separate how data is <strong>used</strong> from how it's <strong>represented</strong>. Constructors and selectors form an abstraction barrier. You can even implement pairs with nothing but functions.</p>
    </div>


    <!-- SVG: Abstraction barrier diagram -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
